<br>
Here's a listing of the RP server rules:<br>
<br>
Quote:<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Everyone at Mythic Entertainment realizes what an exciting and important thing we are doing, as we open our first Roleplaying server. It is important for us to provide the people who really want to Rolepay, with an environment that they can do this in. Therefore, we have come up with several enhancements to our standard Code of Conduct and Disciplinary Policy. These enhancements are intended to make the environments on DAoC roleplaying servers as fun as possible for the people involved, and to dissuade people from coming to the server who are not roleplayers, or people who come to interfere with the roleplaying of others. <br>
One of the main things that will change is our approach to enforcement of the Code of Conduct and Naming Policy. We will be much stricter on our interpretation of these policies and will enforce them with a much heavier hand. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  The message is &quot;Do not come to this server if you do not want to Roleplay&quot;. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->We are very committed to giving excellent customer service on this and all of our game servers, and will do what we can to make playing on the roleplaying servers a great experience for all DAoC roleplayers. <br>
The three main additions to our Policies are outlined below: <br>
<br>
Naming Policy for Rolepaying Servers. <br>
1. All names must fit into the medieval setting. <br>
2. All names must fit into the realm that you are playing in. <br>
All policy enforcement for names on the roleplaying servers will be done aggressively by members of the DAoC CS staff, of Server Lead and higher authority. It is in Mythic's sole judgment whether a name breaks the policy, and we will rename characters accordingly. If you see someone with a name that obviously breaks the roleplaying ruleset, please report them. <br>
<br>
Communication Policy for Roleplaying Server. <br>
1. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  All communication on the roleplay server must be appropriate for the medieval time-period (in-character). This means no talking about Soda-pop, Baseball, etc...</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
2. If a guild, group or person agrees that out-of-character communication is acceptable, then Mythic will not interfere with this decision within /Guild, /Group, /Friend or /Sends communication. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  There is never a time when out-of-character communication is acceptable in /Broadcast, /Say, or /Shout.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
If someone is breaking the roleplaying communication policy on the server, you MUST ask them to stop before reporting them. If they stop when asked, and do not repeat their out-of-character communication, then the problem is solved and there is no need to contact customer support. If someone persists in breaking the roleplaying communication policy, then report them using the /Appeal command, and DAoC Customer Support will investigate. <br>
<br>
Event Interference <br>
1. Any interference or disruption of scheduled events, whether run by players or by Mythic Staff, is strictly prohibited. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  If you cannot abide by these rules, DO NOT play on these servers. Mythic Entertainment has a strict policy of enforcement regarding these rules, and will not tolerate players coming to this server who do not or will not roleplay. Breaking any of the above rules can result in actions against your account to include warnings, banishment from the roleplay servers, suspensions, and even termination of your account (based on the severity of the violation). </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->Thank you and have a great time roleplaying! <br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Followed by:<br>
<br>
Quote:<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 <br>
<br>
I understand everyone's concerns about the RP server, so I want to try and alleviate them as much as possible. <br>
<br>
Communication. <br>
============== <br>
We are NOT looking for grammer, and how you say things (thee's and thou's), we ARE looking for what people say. Talking about things that you would not have talked (or known) about during that time period is the primary offense here. If you are in a group, guild, etc, and everyone agrees that OOC communication is acceptable, then we (Mythic) will not interfere. If you use open channels (/broadcast, /say, etc..) for OOC communication, then you will probably be reported, and a CSR will be in contact with you (because you are violating the policy of the server). <br>
The /Advice channel is indeed where we expect most questions to be asked. The Advisors need to understand that they WILL get OOC communications in this channel, and that it is acceptable. If this does resolve the issue then /Appeal can be used to solve any problems/answer any questions. <br>
<br>
Naming. <br>
======= <br>
Names do not have to be &quot;perfect&quot;. We are looking for names that fit with where and when you are. We figure that if you really want to roleplay, then you are willing to put a little extra thought into a good RP name. We also understand that there is a big fantasy element to our game - &quot;what were Troll's names back then?&quot; is a hard question to answer Again - do your best in the context of the game. Compound, descriptive surnames are definately acceptable (as long as they do not violate any of the other naming policy rules). <br>
<br>
Events. <br>
======= <br>
I will get back to you all on this one. We have definate plans, but I want to make sure that they are firm before I announce anything. <br>
<br>
All in all, we are trying to make a server with an atmosphere that is attractive to people who want to Roleplay, but is decidedly unnatractive to people who want to mess with them. We will be heavy handed in our support of these policies, and for you who honestly want to be there, you should have a great time. For those who don't want to participate in this type of roleplaying, please do not log into this server. <br>
<br>
